data.table explain me how this is intuitive? Subset the group with 1 elem.
Dplyr:
dt <- data.table(a=1:6, g = c(0,1,1,2,2,2))
dt %>% group_by(g) %>%
  filter(n()==1)
D.T:
I'd think that this works:
dt[.N==1, ,by = "g"]
But NO, you need
dt[dt[, .I[.N==1], g]$V1]
